---

<BaseLayout
    title="Getting started — PlasmaZones"
    description="First-run tour for PlasmaZones: verify the install, open the zone editor, and snap your first window."
>
    <main id="main" class="container guide guide-with-sidebar">

        <Sidebar section="plasmazones" />

        <article class="guide-content">

        <Breadcrumb href="/plasmazones/" label="PlasmaZones" />

        <PageHero
            title="Getting started"
            tagline="From install to your first snap in about two minutes."
        />

        <h2 id="verify">Verify the install</h2>
        <p>
            PlasmaZones runs as the <code>plasmazonesd</code>
            user-session daemon. On KDE it also installs a settings
            KCM under Application Management and registers shortcuts
            through KGlobalAccel. Install via the
            <a href="/plasmazones/#install">package for your distro</a>,
            then log out and back in so the shortcuts register.
        </p>
        <Code lang="bash" code={`plasmazonesd --version
# PlasmaZones 2.8.7`} />
        <p class="muted">
            Any Wayland compositor with layer-shell support works.
            X11 was removed in v1.2.0. XWayland apps still snap, but
            autotile's drag-insert is flakier there because XWayland
            emulates input reporting.
        </p>
        <p class="muted">
            On non-KDE compositors (Hyprland, Sway, GNOME, river),
            the daemon registers shortcuts through XDG Portal with a
            D-Bus fallback, and the standalone
            <code>plasmazones-settings</code> app replaces the KCM.
            The
            <a href="https://github.com/fuddlesworth/PlasmaZones/wiki/Compositor-Integration">Compositor
            Integration wiki</a> covers per-compositor setup for
            portable builds without KDE Frameworks.
        </p>

        <h2 id="editor">Open the zone editor</h2>
        <p>
            Press <code>Meta+Shift+E</code>. The editor opens on
            whatever layout is currently assigned to the focused
            screen.
        </p>
        <p>
            Pick a different preset, tweak the gutters, or switch
            to <b>Custom</b> to draw zones freehand. 26 presets
            ship: Master+Stack, BSP, 3-column grid, Fibonacci,
            portrait / ultrawide / super-ultrawide variants,
            priority grid.
        </p>
        <p class="muted">
            Layouts persist as JSON under
            <code>~/.config/plasmazones/</code> with normalized
            0..1 coordinates, so the same layout works at any
            screen size. Three files live there:
            <code>config.json</code> for settings,
            <code>assignments.json</code> for per-screen layouts
            and quick-layout slots,
            <code>session.json</code> for ephemeral state.
        </p>

        <h2 id="first-snap">Your first snap</h2>
        <ol class="step-list">
            <li>Grab any window's title bar.</li>
            <li>
                Hold <code>Alt</code> and the zone overlay fades
                in with the active zones outlined. The modifier
                can be changed in Settings › Input.
            </li>
            <li>
                Drop the window inside a zone and release
                <code>Alt</code>. It resizes to fill the zone.
            </li>
            <li>
                Hold <code>Ctrl+Alt</code> while dragging across
                two adjacent zones to snap across both.
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            <code>Meta+Ctrl+1</code>…<code>Meta+Ctrl+9</code>
            snap the focused window to zones 1–9 directly.
            <code>Alt+Shift+←/→/↑/↓</code> moves focus between
            zones. The <a href="/plasmazones/shortcuts/">shortcut
            reference</a> lists the rest.
        </p>

        <h2 id="multi-screen">Multiple screens and virtual desktops</h2>
        <p>
            Each physical monitor has its own layout. You can
            also subdivide a monitor into up to 10
            <b>virtual screens</b>, each with its own layout,
            autotile state, and settings. Swap between them with
            <code>Meta+Ctrl+Shift+←/→/↑/↓</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Per-desktop layouts are assigned in
            <b>System Settings › Application Management ›
            PlasmaZones › Layouts</b>.
        </p>

        <h2 id="customizing">Customizing</h2>
        <ul class="links">
            <li>
                <a href="/plasmazones/shortcuts/">Shortcut reference →</a>
                <span class="muted">Every default binding and where to rebind it.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/guides/shaders/">Shader authoring guide →</a>
                <span class="muted">
                    Write GLSL for zone highlights and snap
                    previews; drop them into
                    <code>~/.local/share/plasmazones/shaders/</code>
                    and they hot-reload.
                </span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/guides/tiling/">Tiling algorithms guide →</a>
                <span class="muted">
                    Write autotile algorithms in JavaScript and
                    drop them into
                    <code>~/.local/share/plasmazones/algorithms/</code>.
                </span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/plasmazones/from-fancyzones/">Coming from FancyZones →</a>
                <span class="muted">Feature map for PowerToys users.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/plasmazones/troubleshooting/">Troubleshooting →</a>
                <span class="muted">Daemon debug, support reports, the KWin minimum-size window rule.</span>
            </li>
        </ul>

            <PrevNext section="plasmazones" />
        </article>

        <GuideToc entries={toc} />
            </main>
</BaseLayout>
